text: Chaluk or Chalok is a clan originally affiliated with the large Gurjar ethnicity community of India and Pakistan. The Gujjar families who bear this clan name are mostly inhabited in the north Indian states of Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh, Haryana, Uttarakhand, Jammu and Kashmir and Himachal Pradesh. Some are also found in Pakistani-administered Kashmir and Punjab, Pakistan. ==references== Category:Gurjar clans
title: Chaluk
